Description. Male ( holotype from Barmah State Forest, Victoria; WAM
T 65677
):

Prosoma, dorsal shield . Dorsal profile straight in lateral view; shiny dark brown to black; very indistinct darker radial pattern (
Fig. 13
); narrow light median band; covered with sparse black setae, white setae in median band and between PE; black macrosetae around eyes, in particular PE.

Pedipalps (
Figs 15–18
). Prolateral tegular lobe longer than the triangular, membranous tegular apophysis; embolus long and slender, in resting position sitting in cavity of terminal apophysis; terminal apophysis with two lateral tips (
Fig. 18
).

Opisthosoma . Very dark grey; light median longitudinal band with a cover of white setae; otherwise sparse black setae (
Fig. 13
). Venter grey, slightly lighter than dorsally, covered with silver­grey setae. Spinnerets black.

Female ( paratype from Lake Eppalock, Victoria; WAM
T 70050
):

Opisthosoma . As male, but median band very faint (
Fig. 14
).

Epigyne, ventral view (
Fig. 19
). Simple sclerotised plate with a posterior incision.

Epigyne, dorsal view (
Fig. 20
). Spermathecae large, ovoid; copulatory ducts not visible in dorsal view.

Distribution. South­eastern Australia , including New South Wales , South Australia and Victoria (
Fig. 21
).
